# Privacy Policy — Gita Daily

**Last updated: July 2026**

This privacy policy explains how Gita Daily ("the app") handles information.

## Summary

Gita Daily is designed to work entirely on your device. It does not have a
backend server, does not collect analytics, and does not share any
information with the developer or any third party except when you
explicitly choose to use the optional "ask about a problem" feature.

## Information the app stores on your device

- **Daily verse and saved verses**: The full Bhagavad Gita verse dataset is
  bundled inside the app itself. Verses you bookmark ("save") are stored
  locally on your device only.
- **AI provider API keys (optional)**: If you choose to use the "ask about
  a problem" feature, you may enter an API key for Claude (Anthropic),
  Gemini (Google), or ChatGPT (OpenAI). This key is stored only on your
  device, encrypted via the Android Keystore system (EncryptedSharedPreferences).
  The developer never receives, stores, or has access to this key.

## Information sent over the network

The app makes network requests only when you use the optional "ask about a
problem" feature, and only to the AI provider you've selected:

- Your typed question/situation, plus a small set of relevant Bhagavad
  Gita verses (for context), is sent directly from your device to the
  provider's API (Anthropic, Google, or OpenAI — whichever you configured).
- This request is sent using **your own API key**, billed to your own
  account with that provider.
- No copy of this request or its response is sent to, or stored by, the
  developer of this app.

If you do not use this feature, the app makes no network requests at all.

## Third-party services

When you use the "ask about a problem" feature, your request is subject to
the respective provider's own privacy policy and terms of service:

- Anthropic (Claude): https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy
- Google (Gemini): https://policies.google.com/privacy
- OpenAI (ChatGPT): https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy

## Data retention and deletion

- Saved verses and stored API keys remain on your device until you delete
  them within the app's Settings screen, or uninstall the app.
- Uninstalling the app removes all locally stored data associated with it.

## Children's privacy

This app is not directed at children and does not knowingly collect any
information from children.

## Changes to this policy

If this policy changes, an updated version will be posted here with a
